Thanks for the feedback!

I'm hoping it comes across clearly enough that SCP-4000 cannot have a  (or containment), so to speak, and the act of not giving it a specific resting place can possibly be construed as a method of containment. Hence the repetitive and precise (but not concise, as you point out) nature of the article's descriptions.

The connection with the Ark of the Covenant isn't necessarily to imply that the Ark is an anomaly, rather that the Ark can be equated to the circumstances surrounding the aluminum sarcophagus, as does the story of Sisyphus, and the implication SCP-4000 has been in transport to a  for quite some time. This plays into time-related confusions.

I hope that helps clear some things up? This isn't a conventional article by any means. If you have any questions I'd be more than happy to answer them.







