At first, I was rather annoyed by the way this was written, but I think it's actually far more clever than I gave it credit for. That said, it needs some cleanup still and the discovery addendum goes on rather a bit with large paragraphs, making for a bulky ending. There's also probably a little too much Series I-style redaction.

+though

–block


I thought for a bit that the number 4 had significance. Just about everything the Foundation describes itself doing with this comes in fours: four sites a chamber is being constructed, four MTFs, just about everything comes in fours, and you've even got Foresight heading up containment. But after the interview  that seems to go out the window, and I was disappointed by that. I don't know if it was intentional, but it's like you were building up to something and then forgot the payoff.




That said, upvote after the contest.







